{"article_id":"sYH8yVGDVxC8y8GF","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"The Pennsylvania judge","depth":9},{"id":1,"text":"who ruled on Tuesday ,","depth":9},{"id":2,"text":"Robert Simpson of Commonwealth Court , had upheld the law in August","depth":8},{"id":3,"text":"when liberal-leaning and civil rights groups challenged it .","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"But the state ' s Supreme Court instructed him two weeks ago to hold further hearings","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"to focus on whether enough had been done","depth":8},{"id":6,"text":"to ensure \" liberal access \" to the picture ID cards ,","depth":9},{"id":7,"text":"which are available at driver ' s license centers , or alternatives .","depth":9},{"id":8,"text":"Judge Simpson said","depth":6},{"id":9,"text":"that on Nov. 6 , voters in Pennsylvania could be asked to produce the newly required photo ID","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"but ,","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"if they did not have one ,","depth":9},{"id":12,"text":"could still vote on a normal voting machine ,","depth":10},{"id":13,"text":"not using a provisional ballot .","depth":10},{"id":14,"text":"The state may appeal the decision to the State Supreme Court ,","depth":6},{"id":15,"text":"but few predicted victory for it ,","depth":7},{"id":16,"text":"given what the justices had asked of the lower court .","depth":7},{"id":17,"text":"The law ' s opponents said","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"the victory was only a partial one .","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"\" While we ' re happy","depth":11},{"id":20,"text":"that voters in Pennsylvania will not be turned away","depth":12},{"id":21,"text":"if they do not have an ID ,","depth":12},{"id":22,"text":"we are concerned","depth":11},{"id":23,"text":"that the ruling will allow election workers to ask for ID at the polls ,","depth":12},{"id":24,"text":"and this could cause confusion , \"","depth":12},{"id":25,"text":"said Penda D. Hair , co-director of Advancement Project , one of the groups","depth":10},{"id":26,"text":"that challenged the law .","depth":10},{"id":27,"text":"\" This injunction serves as a mere Band-Aid for the law ' s inherent problems , not an effective remedy . \"","depth":8},{"id":28,"text":"Hans von Spakovsky of the Heritage Foundation , a right-of-center research group","depth":11},{"id":29,"text":"that supports the law ,","depth":11},{"id":30,"text":"said :","depth":10},{"id":31,"text":"\" While this may seem to be a win for opponents of common-sense election reform efforts like voter ID ,","depth":10},{"id":32,"text":"it is actually a loss . \"","depth":10},{"id":33,"text":"\" The court simply found","depth":10},{"id":34,"text":"that the state could not effectively implement the ID requirement in only a month , \"","depth":10},{"id":35,"text":"he added .","depth":9},{"id":36,"text":"\" The law is still in place","depth":8},{"id":37,"text":"and remains valid . \"","depth":8},{"id":38,"text":"The Pennsylvania law ,","depth":6},{"id":39,"text":"passed in March","depth":7},{"id":40,"text":"without any Democratic support ,","depth":7},{"id":41,"text":"is one of 11 similar laws around the country","depth":6},{"id":42,"text":"approved by Republican-dominated legislatures .","depth":6},{"id":43,"text":"The laws ' backers say","depth":7},{"id":44,"text":"they are trying to ensure the integrity of the electoral process","depth":8},{"id":45,"text":"by preventing fraud .","depth":8},{"id":46,"text":"But Democrats accuse them of seeking to suppress the votes of the poor and members of minority groups ,","depth":7},{"id":47,"text":"who are less likely to have the needed ID or the means","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"to go to state offices","depth":10},{"id":49,"text":"and obtain one ,","depth":10},{"id":50,"text":"and who tend to vote Democratic .","depth":8},{"id":51,"text":"In opinion surveys , substantial majorities of Americans back the ID requirements","depth":6},{"id":52,"text":"even though repeated efforts","depth":8},{"id":53,"text":"to demonstrate the existence of in-person voter fraud","depth":8},{"id":54,"text":"have found very little .","depth":7},{"id":55,"text":"Newsletter Sign Up","depth":5},{"id":56,"text":"Continue reading the main story","depth":5},{"id":57,"text":"Please verify","depth":7},{"id":58,"text":"you 're not a robot","depth":8},{"id":59,"text":"by clicking the box .","depth":8},{"id":60,"text":"Invalid email address .","depth":7},{"id":61,"text":"Please re-enter .","depth":7},{"id":62,"text":"You must select a newsletter","depth":6},{"id":63,"text":"to subscribe to .","depth":6},{"id":64,"text":"Sign Up","depth":5},{"id":65,"text":"You will receive emails","depth":8},{"id":66,"text":"containing news content , updates and promotions from The New York Times .","depth":8},{"id":67,"text":"You may opt-out at any time .","depth":7},{"id":68,"text":"You agree to receive occasional updates and special offers for The New York Times 's products and services .","depth":7},{"id":69,"text":"Thank you for subscribing .","depth":8},{"id":70,"text":"An error has occurred .","depth":9},{"id":71,"text":"Please try again later .","depth":9},{"id":72,"text":"View all New York Times newsletters .","depth":4},{"id":73,"text":"Pennsylvania is one of a number of swing states","depth":4},{"id":74,"text":"that could make the difference in the race between President Obama and Mitt Romney , the Republican candidate .","depth":4},{"id":75,"text":"Increasingly , however , Mr. Obama ,","depth":6},{"id":76,"text":"who won Pennsylvania in 2008 ,","depth":6},{"id":77,"text":"has been pulling consistently ahead of Mr. Romney in key states .","depth":5},{"id":78,"text":"A Quinnipiac/New York Times/CBS News poll","depth":6},{"id":79,"text":"released last week","depth":6},{"id":80,"text":"showed Mr. Obama ahead in Pennsylvania by 12 points .","depth":5},{"id":81,"text":"The Pennsylvania law ' s challengers said","depth":5},{"id":82,"text":"their focus now would be to press the state to alter its voter education campaign","depth":6},{"id":83,"text":"to make clear","depth":7},{"id":84,"text":"that no picture ID is required in this election .","depth":7},{"id":85,"text":"\" The state has a large budget","depth":8},{"id":86,"text":"to spend","depth":8},{"id":87,"text":"on advertising this fact ,","depth":7},{"id":88,"text":"and we want to make sure","depth":7},{"id":89,"text":"it does it , \"","depth":7},{"id":90,"text":"said Benjamin D. Geffen , a lawyer with the Public Interest Law Center of Philadelphia ,","depth":6},{"id":91,"text":"which took part in the law ' s challenge .","depth":6},{"id":92,"text":"Nick Winkler , director of public relations for Pennsylvania ' s Department of State , said","depth":6},{"id":93,"text":"there would indeed be a change .","depth":6},{"id":94,"text":"\" Our education campaign is in full swing ,","depth":8},{"id":95,"text":"and all","depth":11},{"id":96,"text":"we have to do","depth":11},{"id":97,"text":"is retool it","depth":10},{"id":98,"text":"from talking about requiring voter ID","depth":10},{"id":99,"text":"to requesting it , \"","depth":10},{"id":100,"text":"he said .","depth":7},{"id":101,"text":"\" Poll worker training has not begun in some counties","depth":7},{"id":102,"text":"and will now take this into account as well . \"","depth":7},{"id":103,"text":"The state has issued 13,000 IDs purely for the purpose of voting ,","depth":6},{"id":104,"text":"Mr. Winkler said .","depth":6},{"id":105,"text":"Judge Simpson said in his Tuesday decision","depth":9},{"id":106,"text":"that the issuing of the new documents across the state had not been fast enough .","depth":9},{"id":107,"text":"\" I expected more photo IDs to have been issued by this time , \"","depth":9},{"id":108,"text":"he wrote .","depth":9},{"id":109,"text":"\" Under these circumstances , I am obliged to enter a preliminary injunction \"","depth":8},{"id":110,"text":"preventing the law from being fully carried out .","depth":8},{"id":111,"text":"He said","depth":7},{"id":112,"text":"there might eventually be a full trial","depth":8},{"id":113,"text":"to determine","depth":9},{"id":114,"text":"whether the law could be put into effect in a way","depth":10},{"id":115,"text":"that did not burden voters .","depth":10}],"relations":[{"parent":231,"left":188,"right":230,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":188,"left":170,"right":187,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":170,"left":153,"right":169,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":153,"left":129,"right":152,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":129,"left":123,"right":128,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":123,"left":119,"right":122,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":119,"left":118,"right":3,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":118,"left":117,"right":2,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":117,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":122,"left":4,"right":121,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":121,"left":5,"right":120,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":120,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":128,"left":8,"right":127,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":127,"left":9,"right":126,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":126,"left":10,"right":125,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":125,"left":11,"right":124,"relation":"condition","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":124,"left":12,"right":13,"relation":"mode","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":152,"left":131,"right":151,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":131,"left":14,"right":130,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":130,"left":15,"right":16,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":151,"left":141,"right":150,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":141,"left":132,"right":140,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":132,"left":17,"right":18,"relation":"attribution","nucleari